In nominal phrases, determiners such as articles and demonstratives follow the noun (see Klamer, Schapper and Corbett, \textit{this volume}). All AP languages have clause-final conjunctions; often these are combined with clause-initial ones, as shown in \REF{ex:1:3}, where clause final \textit{a} `and' combines with clause-initial \textit{xabi} `then': 



